Privacy Policy for TapeBoy

Last updated: June 29, 2026

Thank you for using TapeBoy.

TapeBoy respects your privacy. This Privacy Policy explains what information the app accesses and how it is used.

Information We Access

With your permission, TapeBoy may access information from Apple Music using Apple’s MusicKit framework, including:

* Currently playing song
* Artist name
* Album name
* Album artwork
* Playback state

TapeBoy only accesses this information after you grant permission through Apple’s authorization dialog.

How Information Is Used

The information is used solely to provide the app’s features, such as displaying the currently playing track and related artwork.

TapeBoy does not collect, store, or transmit your music library or listening history to any server operated by the developer.

Personal Information

TapeBoy does not collect personally identifiable information.

The app does not sell your personal information.

Data Storage

App preferences and settings are stored locally on your device.

No user accounts are required.

Third-Party Services

TapeBoy uses Apple’s MusicKit framework to access Apple Music content with your permission.

Apple’s collection and processing of data is governed by Apple’s own Privacy Policy.

Children’s Privacy

TapeBoy is not directed toward children under the age of 13 and does not knowingly collect personal information from children.

Changes to This Privacy Policy

This Privacy Policy may be updated from time to time. Any changes will be reflected on this page together with the updated revision date.

